messages.messageBody:
For all of the Warriors lovers, there are also some forums that are devoted to the books.  The ones I'm talking about are role playing forums.  If they like to write they might enjoy being part of them.  My daughter participates in one and really likes it.

If you google "clans of the forest" you'll find a bunch.

Just thought I'd mention them :)

Kelli~
  http://ourjoyfullife.blogspot.com/%c2%a0

"There are no ordinary moments."  Dan Millman,  Peaceful Warrior

messages.messageBody:
Caitlin liked the Seekers book but I'm pretty sure Warriors is her
favorite. She does know about the website and the deviantart site. I
wish I could find some kids around our area that are into the books.
She's obsessed. She has a little video camera that she makes Warrior
movies on with her stuffed animals and she's constantly drawing cat
pictures on MSpaint.

Thanks for all your replies. I already feel a lot more at ease about
it. I'm still learning to trust!!!

messages.messageBody:
<<She went from barely reading to devouring the complete Warriors series
(more than one time!!)>>

Sorscha is rereading the entire series AGAIN (http://www.warriorcats.com/) -
I think this is the third time. She loves the series and is quite upset
that the author 'Erin Hunter' chose to write a polar bear book instead of
focusing on another Warriors book. She's waiting patiently for September
2nd - the release of the newest book in the series.
